commit_message:
Expand help message on config sample file

It may not be obvious to the user that several of the URLs also take a
tenant ID, which needs to be modified based on the environment. Using
the wrong tenant ID leads to problems that are difficult to debug.

subject: Run Validations automatically
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-07 09:14:11.000000000', 'files': ['src/__tests__/actions/RegisterNodesActions.tests.js', 'src/js/actions/CurrentPlanActions.js', 'src/js/components/deployment_plan/DeploymentPlan.js', 'src/js/actions/ValidationsActions.js', 'src/js/actions/RegisterNodesActions.js'], 'message': 'Run Validations automatically

Removes run-validations hints from DeploymentPlan page
Runs pre-deployment and prep validation groups on plan
selection
Runs pre-introspection validation group after nodes are
registered

Additional automatic validations runs will need to be
probably hand-picked to run exact validations at times
it is needed. Running post-deployment validations is
tied to additional deployment progress work

Implements: blueprint automatically-run-validations
Change-Id: I0373f941359fd9e294152bd6db08dee735e2aec4
'}]
commit_message:
Run Validations automatically

Removes run-validations hints from DeploymentPlan page
Runs pre-deployment and prep validation groups on plan
selection
Runs pre-introspection validation group after nodes are
registered

Additional automatic validations runs will need to be
probably hand-picked to run exact validations at times
it is needed. Running post-deployment validations is
tied to additional deployment progress work

Implements: blueprint automatically-run-validations
Change-Id: I0373f941359fd9e294152bd6db08dee735e2aec4

commit_message:
Switch to LBaaS v2 for OpenStack Newton

OpenStack Newton drops support for LBaaS v1; Switch to using the
v2 agent, with associate new template for driver options.

Upgrades from Mitaka will work as the old neutron-lbaas-agent
package will be removed as part of the dist-upgrade to the new
Newton packages and then the new neutron-lbaasv2-agent package
will be installed (as prescribed in the upstream migration
documentation).

Change-Id: I7ef26aca2f86f663366d463aeb3695ff5a402661

commit_message:
Switch to LBaaS v2 for OpenStack Newton

OpenStack Newton drops support for the deprecated v1 LBaaS model;
switch to using LBaaS v2 including directly referencing all
service_providers in the neutron.conf template (implicit loading
from neutron_*.conf files will be removed in Ocata anyway).

Change-Id: I8d625ddf079ed0f0f22d180334b928f04cbae182

commit_message:
Allow getting release id by openstack version field

In upgrade chain scenario we can stuck in release fetching
because after restore of master node we have 3 releases which contains
"Ubuntu 14.04" substrings.
In previous implementation the first matched release is taken (which is Kilo
in upgrade 7-8-9 case instead of Mitaka)
Reusing of RELEASE_VERSION allow us to tune selection process.

Change-Id: Iac2b15fba774b3055016a67528528d8b851dfe16
Partial-bug:1620978

commit_message:
Allow getting release id by openstack version field

In upgrade chain scenario we can stuck in release fetching
because after restore of master node we have 3 releases which contains
"Ubuntu 14.04" substrings.
In previous implementation the first matched release is taken (which is Kilo
in upgrade 7-8-9 case instead of Mitaka)
Reusing of RELEASE_VERSION allow us to tune selection process.

Change-Id: Iac2b15fba774b3055016a67528528d8b851dfe16
Partial-bug:1620978

Some Docker images such as debian:unstable ship a no-op /sbin/initctl
script to prevent docker specific issues with service starting that

Make sure the /sbin/initctl really is "upstart" by checking the output

Change-Id: Ib1021c3374bb4a10eb2bcc3def934205ea1daacd
'}]
commit_message:
Fix init system detection on Docker images

Some Docker images such as debian:unstable ship a no-op /sbin/initctl
script to prevent docker specific issues with service starting that
caused dib-init-system to return "upstart" even if it is not.

Make sure the /sbin/initctl really is "upstart" by checking the output
of `/sbin/initctl --version`.

Change-Id: Ib1021c3374bb4a10eb2bcc3def934205ea1daacd

commit_message:
[WIP] Add support for third party plugins

This commit adds a mechanism to inject snippets of code in Dockerfiles
in order to support third party plugins in Kolla.

The plugins are added to the container image at build time and can be
enabled by specifying an `enabled_xxx_plugins` config option to
`kolla-build.conf` where xxx is the desired image name.

This commit includes a working example for neutron `networking-midonet`
plugin. To enable it, set:

    enabled_neutron_server_plugins="networking-midonet"

Change-Id: Id5a317da2c90ac296b71007f19a05cd313cd35ca
Partially-Implements: blueprint third-party-plugin-support

subject: Fix from_response method to process response from requests
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-07 09:54:45.000000000', 'files': ['ceilometerclient/tests/unit/test_exc.py', 'ceilometerclient/exc.py'], 'message': 'Fix from_response method to process response from requests

SessionClient uses requests library. It's response class doesn't have
"status" property[1], so in case of any errors(with status code > 400),
from_response method is called and raises AttributeError.

Also, HTTPClient implementation uses requests lib by default[2](if 'http'
argument was not transmitted), so from_response method will raise
AttributeError too.

[1] - http://docs.python-requests.org/en/master/api/#requests.Response.status_code
[2] - https://github.com/openstack/python-ceilometerclient/blob/2.6.0/ceilometerclient/openstack/common/apiclient/client.py#L99-L100

Change-Id: Id8fb2f386e8101951716f30a6365c9aa15bd4b24
Closes-Bug: #1620974
(cherry picked from commit 1b1917ab9b56fe92235ce336d3df3e7a8c1c81d2)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix from_response method to process response from requests

SessionClient uses requests library. It's response class doesn't have
"status" property[1], so in case of any errors(with status code > 400),
from_response method is called and raises AttributeError.

Also, HTTPClient implementation uses requests lib by default[2](if 'http'
argument was not transmitted), so from_response method will raise
AttributeError too.

[1] - http://docs.python-requests.org/en/master/api/#requests.Response.status_code
[2] - https://github.com/openstack/python-ceilometerclient/blob/2.6.0/ceilometerclient/openstack/common/apiclient/client.py#L99-L100

Change-Id: Id8fb2f386e8101951716f30a6365c9aa15bd4b24
Closes-Bug: #1620974
(cherry picked from commit 1b1917ab9b56fe92235ce336d3df3e7a8c1c81d2)

commit_message:
Introduce the translator layer

This commit introduces the translation layer to call Neutron API, as
well as the config_map that glues the watcher layer to the translation
layer, and it makes it configurable.

It simplifies a lot the watcher layer, making trivial to create new ones
and relies all the business logic to the translation layer. That
introduces the option to some people extend the project by creating
custom translators by implementing a simple interface and using another
config_map.

Partial-Implements: blueprint kuryr-k8s-integration

commit_message:
Pass storlet language from gateway to daemon factory

This patch enables docker gateway to properly pass the
value of 'X-Object-Meta-Storlet-Language' to daemon
factory, to let daemon factory start python storlet
daemon for python storlets.

NOTE:
This patch also changes the default log level in daemon
factory and sdaemon from TRACE, which is specific in java
logging, to DEBUG, which is common for Java and Python
logging.

Change-Id: I8be37bbdb7c3dfd4d11c855464ecf789932fa354

commit_message:
Trigger the user based policy enforcement by fake rules

The nova deprecated the user based policy enforcement and will emit
warning message when user based policy rule is used. This patch
adds some fake user_based rule on some APIs which didn't support
user_based policy enforcement. The goal is trigger the warning,
to validate that works.

Change-Id: I90c7fc7411ab8452157d2cc74ef9d6d7287e3d04
Depends-On: Iaa9a142ce93a8d13452f0c6318a3d0b54f6220ce

commit_message:
Switch upstream murano puppets to use master branch

Master branch should use current master (currently Newton).
This change is based on top of Murano source code, which exaclty uses
Newton code for Murano plugin codebase.

Workaround:

 - Added class ::openstacklib::defaults which is present in Newton,
   but is not present in Fuel stable/mitaka branch.

Change-Id: I95c3883d886e2decf1c97cb932dfff2f420db3c4

subject: Allow deb-packaging-core to push tags
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-05 07:31:09.000000000', 'files': ['gerrit/acls/openstack/deb-packaging.config'], 'message': 'Allow deb-packaging-core to push tags

We need to push tags to the git, otherwise, we don't have a ref
to build the orig.tar.xz files. For example, Alembic upstream uses
rel_0.6.2, which isn't nice for us. We need to push instead a new
label 0.6.2, which will be used by "git archive" to generate the
tarball.

On top of that, we need to be able to sign normal debian/newton
branch whenever we upload to Debian.

Change-Id: Ib6f9179134abfd38479096de3e99b99a7afe34a0
'}]
commit_message:
Allow deb-packaging-core to push tags

We need to push tags to the git, otherwise, we don't have a ref
to build the orig.tar.xz files. For example, Alembic upstream uses
rel_0.6.2, which isn't nice for us. We need to push instead a new
label 0.6.2, which will be used by "git archive" to generate the
tarball.

On top of that, we need to be able to sign normal debian/newton
branch whenever we upload to Debian.

Pass auth token to diagnostic snapshot dumper

Since Timmy is selfsufficient utility it requires auth token to login to
Fuel to get nodes to dump.
Also getting rid of snapshot configuration unit tests since Timmy
doesn't use most of it.

commit_message:
[WIP] Ironic: Block portgroups

Ironic is landing portgroups in Newton, but Nova is not. To avoid
users from trying to use portgroups with Nova, we must fail early.
This will be removed when portgroups lands in Nova.

Depends-On: Id8afa902026ce4466e96cc7bfb7fb97447d65809

commit_message:
Increase default packet count to 3 in assert_ping

One packet is typically not enough to determine if
an IP is responding since the first could get dropped
during ARP resolution.  Change the default to 3 since
that should be sufficient.

Also, some callers were specifying a timeout of 5
seconds, which isn't all that useful since if the
packet never made it out, waiting longer isn't
going to help.  Let them use the default of 1.

Change-Id: I9c32b7840522fb8e1ce0ea1b2361f5d35e008aae

commit_message:
create release files for consistent and current-tripleo

In ci.centos there are errors on missing release files for the master
and current-tripleo promotion jobs.

reference:
tripleo-quickstart-promote-master-delorean-minimal/563
tripleo-quickstart-promote-master-current-tripleo-delorean-minimal/12

error:
master-current-tripleo.yml' does not exist, or is not readable
master-consistent.yml' does not exist, or is not readable

This fixes the release file names to match the repurpose of the
$LOCATION variable introduced in https://review.gerrithub.io/289818

During the promotion full-deploy.sh will use the proper release files
now pointing to the testing versions of either the consistent or the
current-tripleo images while master will still point to the latest
promoted current-tripleo image.

The $LOCATION variable is now a mandatory parameter for promotion jobs.

Co-Authored-By: Attila Darazs <adarazs@redhat.com>
Change-Id: If893fa4c1cd30980b4c6b840e8459a317ad1a17c

commit_message:
Fix tab navigation in clusters panel

Success urls in views were incorrect.
There is no necessity to determine a
path for concrete tab after successfully
sumbiting form. It's cause of some bugs,
because url link in browser is changed after
submiting form and isn't changed after
change tab.
For example:
If user registers an image, clicks to cluster
tab and refresh page, horizon shows image registry
tab.

Change-Id: I5f35890d8e01de7a574d13cf80de79cb102f3dff
Closes-bug: 1572281

commit_message:
Add RabbitMQ expiration policies for convergence

Right now heat can support convergence mode, means we will give it
chances to raise bug 1599104. We simply add policies for worker queues.
This fix services with interruption signal and leave the target queues
open. The number of queues keep growing by repeat above action.
This patch add a expiration for queues. allow queues to be close as
long as they didn't been used for a long period of time(1 hour).
This fix must solve problem with growing number of RabbitMQ queues.

Change-Id: Icda32000f391780c4e3d5d3ebcc519bf853283b7
Related-Bug: #1599104

[{'number': 5, 'created': '2016-08-31 07:47:06.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/emc/vnx/client.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/volume/drivers/emc/vnx/mocked_cinder.yaml', 'cinder/volume/drivers/emc/vnx/adapter.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/volume/drivers/emc/vnx/mocked_vnx.yaml', 'cinder/tests/unit/volume/drivers/emc/vnx/test_adapter.py'], 'message': "Performance issue for VNX attache LUN

The VNX driver experience some performance issue during initialize
connection.

After some analysis, we root caused the problem to two issues.
1. Storage group instance was retrieved every time it's needed.  Extra
CLI calls were made to update the host LUN information in the storage
group.  These CLI calls could be saved if we cache the storage group
instance in the client.
2. Storage group instance was force updated even though we didn't do
any configuration update for the initiator port map.  This is an
implementation error.  Use `any` to check whether the list of updated
initiator port map is empty or not and do not call force update if it's
empty.

Change-Id: I6f101a73d07cb58859ff25aad9411f18b67aa67f
Co-Authored-By: Ryan Liang <ryan.liang@emc.com>
Closes-Bug: #1615621
"}]
commit_message:
Performance issue for VNX attache LUN

The VNX driver experience some performance issue during initialize
connection.

After some analysis, we root caused the problem to two issues.
1. Storage group instance was retrieved every time it's needed.  Extra
CLI calls were made to update the host LUN information in the storage
group.  These CLI calls could be saved if we cache the storage group
instance in the client.
2. Storage group instance was force updated even though we didn't do
any configuration update for the initiator port map.  This is an
implementation error.  Use `any` to check whether the list of updated
initiator port map is empty or not and do not call force update if it's
empty.

Change-Id: I6f101a73d07cb58859ff25aad9411f18b67aa67f
Co-Authored-By: Ryan Liang <ryan.liang@emc.com>
Closes-Bug: #1615621

show all available branches in list-changes

We show the branches a release is coming from, but not what branches
exist. During the period right after a new stable branch is created, it
can be helpful to have the full list for review.

Change-Id: Ic14d3b4ca6631558988b74d27cfb1cdebb056c67
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

subject: Fix from_response method to process response from requests
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-07 09:45:31.000000000', 'files': ['ceilometerclient/tests/unit/test_exc.py', 'ceilometerclient/exc.py'], 'message': 'Fix from_response method to process response from requests

SessionClient uses requests library. It's response class doesn't have
"status" property[1], so in case of any errors(with status code > 400),
from_response method is called and raises AttributeError.

Also, HTTPClient implementation uses requests lib by default[2](if 'http'
argument was not transmitted), so from_response method will raise
AttributeError too.

[1] - http://docs.python-requests.org/en/master/api/#requests.Response.status_code
[2] - https://github.com/openstack/python-ceilometerclient/blob/2.6.0/ceilometerclient/openstack/common/apiclient/client.py#L99-L100

Change-Id: Id8fb2f386e8101951716f30a6365c9aa15bd4b24
Closes-Bug: #1620974
'}]
commit_message:
Fix from_response method to process response from requests

SessionClient uses requests library. It's response class doesn't have
"status" property[1], so in case of any errors(with status code > 400),
from_response method is called and raises AttributeError.

Also, HTTPClient implementation uses requests lib by default[2](if 'http'
argument was not transmitted), so from_response method will raise
AttributeError too.

[1] - http://docs.python-requests.org/en/master/api/#requests.Response.status_code
[2] - https://github.com/openstack/python-ceilometerclient/blob/2.6.0/ceilometerclient/openstack/common/apiclient/client.py#L99-L100

Change-Id: Id8fb2f386e8101951716f30a6365c9aa15bd4b24
Closes-Bug: #1620974

rather than two instructions: get() and del, giving the codes a format
that carries through.

commit_message:
Add event configuration for event trigger

When using event trigger feature, some of the notification data may be
useful to end users in their workflows. However, the whole data can not
be visible to end users due to security reasons.

This patch will give operators a chance to define what information will
be available to end users. If the definition is not found, a 'safe'
default setting will be used.

Change-Id: I8b6e9cbe318011d2d11a2bb91aaff4d37222c7eb
Implements: blueprint event-notification-trigger

commit_message:
Adds neutron_lbaas.conf to q-svc command line

When q-lbaasv2 is enabled in local.conf, the neutron-lbaas plugin.sh script
creates a new /etc/neutron/neutron_lbaas.conf file with some config parameters.

Under several circumstances, some of the options in this file are needed by
other neutron daemons, such as the q-svc service.

This patch adds a check to examine if q-lbaasv2 is enabled (excluding octavia),
And on such cases, it makes sure that the command-line for the q-svc service
will also include '--config-file /etc/neutron/neutron_lbaas.conf' so that these
configuration parameters are pulled in for that service.

Change-Id: Ia57cc4acd7bca2711b6f0449dd3443a62ddd9c95
Closes-Bug: #1619466
Related-Bug: #1565511

commit_message:
Added mount_opts argument to mount_fs method

On centos bootstrap we don't able to mount images without
'-o loop' option in mount command because of old version of
util-linux-ng package. That's why mount_opts argument in mount_fs
method is needed in order to set options for mount command.

Change-Id: I18017ea0dfd782eef3d331c81686d304abaf3d8d
Closes-Bug: #1620998

commit_message:
Enable parallel job execution for the scheduler to allow abort signals

Now the scheduler uses two pools of resources to handle execution of jobs.
The first one will handle the polling of jobs from the api.
The second one will handle the job exection. This way we avoid blocking the
scheduler while running jobs.

Abort a running job is now enabled thanks to the parallel execution.

Depends-on: I9e92ccdd7c592a8109fe8398db6d53c9c42dc10a
Closes-bug: 1615662
Change-Id: I48153dcb521b6a8f0138d5ef81239cf4cded4df0

commit_message:
Forbid legacy tasks only in LCM enabled clusters

In case we inherit old clusters, without LCM, we must not check their
plugins for legacy tasks to prohibit them.

Change-Id: I23dcc48cc1321d38666b8bcf7d435abd70ac9b61

commit_message:
Do not remove logs on 'tox -e cleanup'

So far we call `tox -e cleanup` each time before running Fuel UI test.
We need that to clear database and start fresh Nailgun instance.
Unfortunately, tox's cleanup goal removes Nailgun logs and at the end of
tests we have only logs from last running test case.

In order avoid this inconvenient and provide full logs on CI, let's stop
removing those logs.

Change-Id: I43107a2de4bf0656e3cec3e924bf55c55f0beacb

commit_message:
Return 404 when a secret does not have a payload

Currently when a Secret payload GET is performed, a 500 Error will
be thrown if there is no payload present. The correct behavior
would be to throw a 404.

Closes-Bug: #1590972
Change-Id: Ibbe8a592c853fc0196ae7c2daf365754c800fc87
(cherry picked from commit d9b5ac8295d096382ccf531e0e5126fba202b217)

commit_message:
Add get_endpoint() method to v2 client

There is no way to check if the endpoint exists with
neutron v2 client when using sessions  other than
client.httpclient.get_endpoint()

We should wrap this like the get_auth_info.

Change-Id: If8c4411c2db4521bda35c2aa6dc63d9df9a90a8b

commit_message:
Warn user about enforce_type default change

We plan to change the enforce_type default to True.
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/328692

But this is going to break some project. This change
adds a deprecation warning to help them to track their broken
tests.

This should avoid people to change ton of tests file in all projects for
no real value. Specially for an option that in this end will be removed
from oslo.config when everybody have switched to the enforcing mode.

Related-Bug: #1517839

Change-Id: I438aeb766d663dbfe5dbd263fd166c25814204e8

Colorize output on tty only

Check ConsoleHandler stream for tty and colorize only if True.
On CI colorized output is not processed and metacharacters
simply reproduced in output as-is.

commit_message:
Implement Python SDaemon

This patch introduces the first implementation of the python
sdaemon, which invokes storlet application written in python,
inside storlet container.

NOTE:
Currently python sdaemon does not load storlet applications,
and returns metadata/content without any change, to just test
process launching and fd handling first.
Application loading support is going to be implemented in
another patch.

Change-Id: I7cd51965952b53058f5a27b1193058a2fbe54d02
Implements: blueprint python-storlet

commit_message:
Fixing pep8.
Use proxy variables just if explicit configured on settings. Without use
this settings detect client IP address using 'REMOTE_ADDR'.
The settings variable created to check HTTP_X_REAL_IP and
HTTP_X_FORWARDED_FOR is 'HORIZON_BEHIND_PROXY'.

Change-Id: I5585e038bdd3d8047737c05082eef1ff3f1b1a96

subject: Show resource name path in event log formatter
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-06 01:54:29.000000000', 'files': ['heatclient/tests/unit/test_utils.py', 'heatclient/osc/v1/event.py', 'heatclient/common/utils.py', 'heatclient/common/event_utils.py'], 'message': "Show resource name path in event log formatter

The resource name path was introduced in the 'openstack stack failures'
command and is a user-friendly way of referring to a deeply nested
resource.

This change modifies the event log formatter to build and display the
resource name path for each event based only off data in previous
events.

For building the full resource path, and omitting ugly stack names
from the resource path, the following heat change is needed
Ib8feb7752bd5736785d142216312bb35629b3601. However the output is still
improved slightly when running against an older heat which does not
have this change.

Change-Id: I86b687fc516da215a6baeef8b365a520d12a8ab1
Closes-Bug: #1619415
"}]
commit_message:
Show resource name path in event log formatter

The resource name path was introduced in the 'openstack stack failures'
command and is a user-friendly way of referring to a deeply nested
resource.

This change modifies the event log formatter to build and display the
resource name path for each event based only off data in previous
events.

For building the full resource path, and omitting ugly stack names
from the resource path, the following heat change is needed
Ib8feb7752bd5736785d142216312bb35629b3601. However the output is still
improved slightly when running against an older heat which does not
have this change.

Change-Id: I86b687fc516da215a6baeef8b365a520d12a8ab1
Closes-Bug: #1619415

commit_message:
Move puppet-tripleo to TripleO

puppet-tripleo was owned by Puppet OpenStack and TripleO teams but the
actual users and developers are TripleO folks.

In term of ownership it would make sense to move it into TripleO
governance.
It will mean that it will be released in same time as other TripleO
projects and also core reviewed by TripleO developers.

Change-Id: I4dbf15dc32b27ab8e54058445384887e4a97e0ba

commit_message:
change training-labs release model to none

training-labs hasn't tagged a release since kilo and it doesn't seem to
be using standard versioning (I see "eol" tags). Change the release
model to "none" to remove it from several auto-generated release team
dashboards and checklists.

Change-Id: I620c981ea3699f09c062ddf34469ac776ac8f49c
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Stop using mox in test_wsgi, test_nexenta, test_netapp

As mox is not compatible with python 3, all test cases that use
mox should be updated to use mock instead.

Replaced stubs.Set() with mock_object() in some classes.

Change-Id: I0556a9188ef767c8b29b091a638499dbeec6e332

commit_message:
Add VIP names to allNodesConfig

The nodes need to be aware of the fqdn's for the specific endpoints
in the cloud. This could be either to set the entries in /etc/hosts
or to select an appropriate hostname for a certificate to be
generated.

bp tls-via-certmonger

Change-Id: I9b4645b937a344f46ec18a9a68c5afa2bc5206d0

subject: Raise NotImplementedError instead of NotImplemented
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-03 02:13:38.000000000', 'files': ['networking_bgpvpn_heat/bgpvpnservice.py'], 'message': 'Raise NotImplementedError instead of NotImplemented

NotImplementedError is the name of the exception
(https://docs.python.org/2/library/exceptions.html).
NotImplemented is the name of a constant
(https://docs.python.org/2/library/constants.html).

>>> raise NotImplemented()
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<pyshell#31>", line 1, in <module>
    raise NotImplemented()
TypeError: 'NotImplementedType' object is not callable
>>> raise NotImplementedError()
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<pyshell#32>", line 1, in <module>
    raise NotImplementedError()
NotImplementedError
 This patch fix it.

Change-Id: I5f38f34f59ffed87baa9269aa0f7b848bcacc8fa
Closes-Bug: #1339855
'}]
commit_message:
Raise NotImplementedError instead of NotImplemented

NotImplementedError is the name of the exception
(https://docs.python.org/2/library/exceptions.html).
NotImplemented is the name of a constant
(https://docs.python.org/2/library/constants.html).

>>> raise NotImplemented()
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<pyshell#31>", line 1, in <module>
    raise NotImplemented()
TypeError: 'NotImplementedType' object is not callable
>>> raise NotImplementedError()
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<pyshell#32>", line 1, in <module>
    raise NotImplementedError()
NotImplementedError
 This patch fix it.

Change-Id: I5f38f34f59ffed87baa9269aa0f7b848bcacc8fa

commit_message:
Add more tempest tests for read permissions

* Improve the set of tests to be more exhaustive. The goal of these tests is
  to check that the reading restrictions between user of different tenants
  are preserved.
* The tests added are:
  * show bgpvpn object made by a non owner fail.
  * show network association made by a non owner fail.
  * list network associations made by a non owner fail.
* Add new methods to the BgpvpnClient (list, show).
* Rename some methods/calls to be more standard.

Change-Id: I7a3d773b30aa4ceaf13022f200f6fc6a49934ec2
Partial-Bug: #1607664

commit_message:
Allow galera to listen on v4/v6

While working on https://review.openstack.org/#/c/320542/, galera
was found to be listening only on IPv6 addresses. Connections to
::1 worked fine, but connections to 127.0.0.1 failed.

This patch ensures that galera is listening on all IPv4 and IPv6
addresses.

commit_message:
drop non-I/O threading in upgrade

threading does nothing in python unless the task is heavily
I/O-dependent. we already use threads to retrieve data so we
really shouldn't wrap entire upgrade step in threading as it doesn't
offer any benefits.

Partial-Bug: #1600796
Change-Id: Ia4e834e6566cf053b9f26b2bee9142dff0c72444

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-02 19:15:57.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/api/compute/volumes/test_attach_volume.py'], 'message': "Narrow assertion in attach/delete volume test

The attach_delete_volume test takes the device name
from tempest.conf's volume_device_name and looks for the output
in /proc/partition.  It could be that this name occurs in part of
another partition's string.  Patch adjusts the name used in the

commit_message:
Narrow assertion in attach/delete volume test

The attach_delete_volume test takes the device name
from tempest.conf's volume_device_name and looks for the output
in /proc/partition.  It could be that this name occurs in part of
another partition's string.  Patch adjusts the name used in the
assertion to make sure it's an exact match.

Change-Id: I570864c7c38969dcdcbfa5bd71be0348d90bd790
Closes-Bug: #1619564

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-11-19 12:46:28.000000000', 'files': ['glance/tests/unit/test_migrations.py', 'glance/tests/functional/db/test_simple.py', 'glance/tests/integration/v2/test_property_quota_violations.py', 'glance/async/flows/base_import.py'], 'message': "test: make enforce_type=True in CONF.set_override

Current Glance uses method CONF.set_override to change config option's
value with designated value in unit test, but never check if the
designated vaule is valid. Each config option has a type like strOpt,
BoolOpt, etc. StrOpt with parameter choices only allows values in set
of choices. In short word, each config option has limitation for type
and value. In production code, oslo.conf can ensure user's input is
valid, but in unit test, test methods can pass if we use method
CONF.set_override without parameter enforce_type=True even we pass wrong
type or wrong value to config option. This commit makes sure calling
method CONF.set_override with enforce_type=True,

Note: We can't set enforce_type=True by default in oslo.config now, it
may break all project's unit test. We can switch enforce_type=True by
default when all project fix violations like this commit.

Change-Id: I2defdfff3b14828133921e97acfea6b08c8fc20a
Related-Bug: #1517839
"}]
commit_message:
test: make enforce_type=True in CONF.set_override

Current Glance uses method CONF.set_override to change config option's
value with designated value in unit test, but never check if the
designated vaule is valid. Each config option has a type like strOpt,
BoolOpt, etc. StrOpt with parameter choices only allows values in set
of choices. In short word, each config option has limitation for type
and value. In production code, oslo.conf can ensure user's input is
valid, but in unit test, test methods can pass if we use method
CONF.set_override without parameter enforce_type=True even we pass wrong
type or wrong value to config option. This commit makes sure calling
method CONF.set_override with enforce_type=True,

Note: We can't set enforce_type=True by default in oslo.config now, it
may break all project's unit test. We can switch enforce_type=True by
default when all project fix violations like this commit.

subject: Add __ne__ built-in function
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-05 01:09:16.000000000', 'files': ['anchor/auth/results.py'], 'message': 'Add __ne__ built-in function

In Python 3 __ne__ by default delegates to __eq__ and inverts the
result, but in Python 2 they urge you to define __ne__ when you
define __eq__ for it to work properly [1].There are no implied
relationships among the comparison operators. The truth of x==y
does not imply that x!=y is false. Accordingly, when defining __eq__(),
one should also define __ne__() so that the operators will behave
as expected.
[1]https://docs.python.org/2/reference/datamodel.html#object.__ne__

Change-Id: Iebabc4deea0aadbec4e73aae52e78bfd84209379
'}]
commit_message:
Add __ne__ built-in function

In Python 3 __ne__ by default delegates to __eq__ and inverts the
result, but in Python 2 they urge you to define __ne__ when you
define __eq__ for it to work properly [1].There are no implied
relationships among the comparison operators. The truth of x==y
does not imply that x!=y is false. Accordingly, when defining __eq__(),
one should also define __ne__() so that the operators will behave
as expected.
[1]https://docs.python.org/2/reference/datamodel.html#object.__ne__

Change-Id: Iebabc4deea0aadbec4e73aae52e78bfd84209379

commit_message:
Fixed dead-locks and race conditions in tasks execution

Also imporved detecting dead-locks in chains, instead
of card-coded chains use generic approach - collect
knowledge about chains and check a new one against
knowledge base.

subject: Add validation logic for python storlets
revisions:
[{'number': 11, 'created': '2016-09-06 13:50:26.000000000', 'files': ['Engine/swift/storlet_gateway/gateways/docker/gateway.py', 'tests/unit/swift/storlet_gateway/gateways/docker/test_gateway.py'], 'message': 'Add validation logic for python storlets

This patch adds validation logic specific for python storlet files,
to support python as a language to write Storlet applications.

The validation logic is based on based on the following rule.
 1. the object should be a python file, whose name ends with .py
 2. X-Object-Meta-Storlet-Main should indicate the class name
    in the python file

Currently it only supports singile python file, but we also have
a plan to let it support bdist tar file in the future.

Implements: blueprint python-storlet
Change-Id: I58d0417d68f4da0afe4ef9dc5008a1c16a9b71a8
'}]
commit_message:
Add validation logic for python storlets

This patch adds validation logic specific for python storlet files,
to support python as a language to write Storlet applications.

The validation logic is based on based on the following rule.
 1. the object should be a python file, whose name ends with .py
 2. X-Object-Meta-Storlet-Main should indicate the class name
    in the python file

Currently it only supports singile python file, but we also have
a plan to let it support bdist tar file in the future.

Implements: blueprint python-storlet
Change-Id: I58d0417d68f4da0afe4ef9dc5008a1c16a9b71a8

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-08-09 11:17:27.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/common/custom_matchers.py', 'tempest/api/object_storage/test_account_services.py'], 'message': 'Fix checks for content length in object storage tests.

Tempest verifies whether HTTP response have "Content-Length"
header specified. However, the checks do not have exceptions
for the cases clearly mentioned in the RFC 7230:

  "A server MUST NOT send a Content-Length header field in
  any response with a status code of 1xx (Informational) or
  204 (No Content)."

This patch rectifies the checks to not enforce presence of
the Content-Length in such cases.

Change-Id: I725982dbcf1f1ea4ffb2bb7106aefdd3029d3e03
Closes-Bug: #1536251
'}]
commit_message:
Fix checks for content length in object storage tests.

Tempest verifies whether HTTP response have "Content-Length"
header specified. However, the checks do not have exceptions
for the cases clearly mentioned in the RFC 7230:

  "A server MUST NOT send a Content-Length header field in
  any response with a status code of 1xx (Informational) or
  204 (No Content)."

This patch rectifies the checks to not enforce presence of
the Content-Length in such cases.

Change-Id: I725982dbcf1f1ea4ffb2bb7106aefdd3029d3e03
Closes-Bug: #1536251

commit_message:
Add tempest to keystone role tests

The keystone functional tests are currently not using tempest, and are
quite lacking in functionality.

This PR adds tempest testing to the keystone role.
We use the tempest.api.identity tests but exclude the tests for
credentials and ec2 which we don't currently support.

TODO: (andymccr)
We need to add support for these (and remove the exclusion) by
performing a 'keystone-manage credential_setup --keystone-user keystone
--keystone-group keystone'

Change-Id: I9a7207e75040c304c53820795cb66ce9be00c350

commit_message:
Fix a race with auto_schedule of HA routers

When creating an HA router, after the server creates all the DB objects
(including the HA network and ports if it's the first one), the server
continues on the schedule the router to (some of) the available agents.

The race is achieved when an L3 agent router issues a
get_router_ids/sync_routers request, which later down the line ends up
in an auto_schedule_routers() call. If this happens before the above
schedule (of the create_router()) is complete, the server will refuse
to schedule the router to the other intended L3 agents, resulting is
less agents being scheduled. This patch adds a check to make sure that
such failures will rollback silently and not cause the router to not be
created.

Closes-Bug: #1605282
Change-Id: If684326f213685e406415f42f84d94d2c2af344f

commit_message:
Enable HiPE compile configuration

The ``rabbitmq_server`` role now supports configuring HiPE compilation
of the RabbitMQ server Erlang code. This configuration option may improve
server performance for some workloads and hardware. Deployers can
override the ``rabbitmq_hipe_compile`` variable, setting a value of
``True`` if they wish to enable this feature.

Change-Id: I433d94eff00ac82a9069f9092faa87d449190442

commit_message:
ML2: improve performance of get_networks

In the event that fields are not requested we do not iterate
over the list of retrieved networks. In the case that an admin
user is reading thousands of networks this can be very helpful.

Related-Bug: #1611626

The initial patch fixes Mismatch error returned by attach/detach

commit_message:
Count volumes vs partitions and remove hard-coded expected result

The initial patch fixes Mismatch error returned by attach/detach
shelved_or_offload_server Tempest tests because of counting disk
partitions instead of volumes.

Along with counting volumes instead of partitions, the current patch
proposes to remove hard-coded expected result from tests mentioned
above, since it may lead to another Mismatch errors. It may happen,
if an Openstack environment is configured with force_config_drive=True
(at least, this option is enabled in devstack at the moment), and if
it's configured to use block device for config drive instead of
loopback disk file, which is not expected by mentioned tests.
The proposed fix makes these tests more flexible and independent from
environments with specific configurations.
Also, the _create_and_attach() helper function has been splitted onto
smaller pieces to move some of them where they are really used and
to make the whole logic of the test suit cleaner.

Co-Authored-By: Anna Babich <ababich@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: I4736dc9292affa7374e72cba4e3309c1330ebabd
Closes-Bug: #1595503

commit_message:
Add --dry-run option to nailgun-agent

It's a bit hard to debug nailgun-agent, because it
tries to send info over http somewhere and sleeps at
the beginning. So you can't run it on your desktop, for
example.

Let's add --dry-run option, to have ability to just get
and print all information.

This is a small improvement, so no bug or blueprint.

Change-Id: If7309635d40ff3263a671fddd7df20efd917097c

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-07 05:36:27.000000000', 'files': ['test/test_pyeclib_api.py', 'pyeclib/ec_iface.py'], 'message': "Fix arg k, m to be required

Right now ECDriver doesn't check if k, m exist in the kwargs for init.
That can tigger unfortunately success to init and that will fail at
encode/decode (or result in odd with get_segment_info)

Once, we have jerasure_rs_vand in default, that worked becuase jerasure
did the assertion for the k, m parameters but we can reproduce the
failures which this patch want fix with like:

driver = ECDriver(ec_type='liberasurecode_rs_vand')   # <- this is
default and it succeeded!
driver.encode(' ')  # <- And then, this will result in ECDriverError:
Out of memory, whooa!

This patch fixes this to check the k, m existence in the init process.

Change-Id: I0757c0a4e510ba42f357db0cac22861919d0ca26
"}]
commit_message:
Fix arg k, m to be required

Right now ECDriver doesn't check if k, m exist in the kwargs for init.
That can tigger unfortunately success to init and that will fail at
encode/decode (or result in odd with get_segment_info)

Once, we have jerasure_rs_vand in default, that worked becuase jerasure
did the assertion for the k, m parameters but we can reproduce the
failures which this patch want fix with like:

driver = ECDriver(ec_type='liberasurecode_rs_vand')   # <- this is
default and it succeeded!
driver.encode(' ')  # <- And then, this will result in ECDriverError:
Out of memory, whooa!

This patch fixes this to check the k, m existence in the init process.

Change-Id: I0757c0a4e510ba42f357db0cac22861919d0ca26

commit_message:
EMC VMAX - multi-attach failure to VMAX3 when SLO is omitted

An SLO of NONE is a valid FAST configuration so when the SLO was
not included in the xml file we assigned NONE to it. The omission
of SLO should mean Non FAST in VMAX3, similar to how VMAX2 is
implemented.

Change-Id: I6cafd45d0f2584c0cc2aba427546c153ca53a101
Closes-Bug: #1567577

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-29 11:30:32.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/driver.py'], 'message': "Fix the password print in cinder-volume.log issue

In cinder.conf replication_device may contains replication
remote device password,and in cinder.volume.driver secret
is not set 'true' for replication_device, So when start cinder
volume service,replication remote device sensitive information
will print in cinder volume log, it will cause some security
problems.

This commit fixes that by setting secret=true for replication_device
in cinder.volume.driver.

Change-Id: I710b557768ca3df0303d70b43b3c74247eed6b24
Closes-Bug: #1617534
"}]
commit_message:
Fix the password print in cinder-volume.log issue

In cinder.conf replication_device may contains replication
remote device password,and in cinder.volume.driver secret
is not set 'true' for replication_device, So when start cinder
volume service,replication remote device sensitive information
will print in cinder volume log, it will cause some security
problems.

This commit fixes that by setting secret=true for replication_device
in cinder.volume.driver.

Change-Id: I710b557768ca3df0303d70b43b3c74247eed6b24
Closes-Bug: #1617534

commit_message:
Import mox in __init__.py

We can initialize the 'mox' of module mox3 in __init__.py,
then in these files that have modified, we only have
'import mox' other than 'from mox3 import mox', which can
make the code smaller and clear.

Change-Id: Ic09597a7205eed47bd3cff03d1e7bc78744e52d4

commit_message:
Remove unused elements

The maintenance burden of so many unused elements which are subject to
bit-rot is large.

I'd like them to be deleted so the scope of change to convert the
remaining elements to being purely package based is more obvious.

The delete list was determined by building a resolved dependency list
from the current tripleoclient image build.

However tripleo-image-elements appears to be branchless, its not clear
what stable image building is depending on currently unused elements
(other than rdo-release, which is left alone in this commit)

Change-Id: I0699005076beaa1644e527032c202c07855a376d

subject: Fix bad use of jsonify() in _get_data
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-30 20:40:40.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_health/api.py'], 'message': 'Fix bad use of jsonify() in _get_data

When no test runs are found in the subunit2sql database we attempt to
return an empty result set in get_test_runs_for_test. However, in the
cached function _get_data() the empty response was wrapped in a
call to jsonify() causing the function to return a Response rather
than a serializable dict.

This patch removes the bad jsonify() call to avoid any serialization
errors for pages with no data.

Change-Id: I49d47bb998593f61fc4b1431d366c4cdd9bb3d2c
'}]
commit_message:
Fix bad use of jsonify() in _get_data

When no test runs are found in the subunit2sql database we attempt to
return an empty result set in get_test_runs_for_test. However, in the
cached function _get_data() the empty response was wrapped in a
call to jsonify() causing the function to return a Response rather
than a serializable dict.

This patch removes the bad jsonify() call to avoid any serialization
errors for pages with no data.

Change-Id: I49d47bb998593f61fc4b1431d366c4cdd9bb3d2c

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-08-16 23:12:33.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/conf/saml.py'], 'message': 'Set default value for [saml]/idp_contact_surname

The keystone federation configuration documentation[1] says that the
Contact options are "advisable" to set, but not strictly necessary.
However, without this patch, the keystone SAML IdP will generate
metadata where one of its tags is malformed:

  <ns0:SurName />

On a Shibboleth-based keystone SP, shibd will successfully start but
fail to retrieve metadata from the IdP, with the message:

  ERROR OpenSAML.MetadataProvider.XML : metadata instance failed manual validation checking: SurName must have TextContent.

Attempting to exchange the SAML assertion will then fail with a 500
error.

While it is advisable for the user to set this surname value, it should
not be strictly necessary, especially in a developer or
proof-of-concept environment. This patch gives the config option a
default value, similar to the other [saml]/idp_contact_* default values.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/keystone/configure_federation.html#configuration-options

Change-Id: I2742f6b4747f1dc5f5593afae1cfde4e494b7848
'}]
commit_message:
Set default value for [saml]/idp_contact_surname

The keystone federation configuration documentation[1] says that the
Contact options are "advisable" to set, but not strictly necessary.
However, without this patch, the keystone SAML IdP will generate
metadata where one of its tags is malformed:

  <ns0:SurName />

On a Shibboleth-based keystone SP, shibd will successfully start but
fail to retrieve metadata from the IdP, with the message:

  ERROR OpenSAML.MetadataProvider.XML : metadata instance failed manual validation checking: SurName must have TextContent.

Attempting to exchange the SAML assertion will then fail with a 500
error.

While it is advisable for the user to set this surname value, it should
not be strictly necessary, especially in a developer or
proof-of-concept environment. This patch gives the config option a
default value, similar to the other [saml]/idp_contact_* default values.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/keystone/configure_federation.html#configuration-options

Change-Id: I2742f6b4747f1dc5f5593afae1cfde4e494b7848

commit_message:
Emit log message for fernet tokens only

A previous refactor improved some of the logging we had when loading Fernet
keys. The log message makes sense from a token perspective since
`max_active_keys` is configured for the fernet token provider. For the
credential provider, it doesn't necessarily make sense because we don't expose
a `max_active_keys` option through configuration.

This commit makes it so the we only emit the log message when it is referencing
a fernet token key repository.

Change-Id: Iad04bd1340a9a59c465337dedcfcd1ea0bed4bde

commit_message:
Fix middleware order of proxy pipeline and add missing modules

This patch fixes the order of the middlewares defined in the Swift proxy
server pipeline.

Sources for the order:
https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/master/etc/proxy-server.conf-sample#L91-L99
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/swift/middleware.html#
https://github.com/openstack/swift3/blob/master/etc/proxy-server.conf-sample#L9
https://github.com/openstack/ceilometermiddleware/blob/master/ceilometermiddleware/swift.py#L21-L22

These are all values in order:

 10 catch_errors
 20 gatekeeper
 30 healthcheck
 40 (reserved for proxy_logging, see below)
 50 cache
 60 container_sync
 70 swift3
 80 s3token
 90 ratelimit
100 crossdomain
110 bulk
120 tempurl
130 formpost
140 copy
150 tempauth
160 swauth
170 authtoken
180 keystone
190 staticweb
200 copy
210 account_quotas
220 container_quotas
230 slo
240 dlo
250 versioned_writes
260 ceilometer
270 proxy-logging
280 proxy-server

The copy and versioned_writes middlewares have been added too.

The proxy_logging should be added a second time at position 40, but the
actual value is 270 to have the final proxy-logging just before the
proxy-server.

Also renamed the suffix 'swauth' in the 'tempauth' manifest to be
'tempauth'; 'swauth' is used in a different manifest.

Closes-Bug: 1618514
Change-Id: I99433720e32dc3557b809c8d42ce3d5981c199c3

commit_message:
Add skip logic for admin cred in test_auto_allocate_network

In case tests are being run with pre provisioned account and
admin cred are not defined then auto allocate network tests
which needs admin cred for tenant isolation should be skipped
instead of fail.

Those tests are not derived from admin base class(which is valid)
so we need to explicitly have the skip logic based on availability
of admin cred.

Change-Id: I3f0472665d7645986ee101390c8e406668a1567b

commit_message:
Fix using filter() to meet python2,3

As mentioned in link[1], if we need filter on python3,
Replace filter(lambda obj: test(obj), data) with:
[obj for obj in data if test(obj)].

[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3

Change-Id: I41e56269ee4c8b1d6bd4dcb3d576d51d24b98aea

commit_message:
Return 404 when a secret does not have a payload

Currently when a Secret payload GET is performed, a 500 Error will
be thrown if there is no payload present. The correct behavior
would be to throw a 404.

Change-Id: Ibbe8a592c853fc0196ae7c2daf365754c800fc87
Partial-Bug: #1561701

commit_message:
fix systemd resource deadlock

Dependency to start network-pre (which
depends on network.target) before
dhcp-interface@.service collides with
Ubuntu's own network.target that suupose
to start after network-pre.

Change-Id: I9e59c970bfb1ebdaa15b4ec6b545761ede3ca056
Closes-bug: #1619816

commit_message:
Template validation/gating

This adds support to the tests/gate for checking if all the
templates are valid yaml. If they have alpha init-containers,
check if they are valid json.

It also fixes a few broken links in the service catalog that
the tests discovered were broken.

Change-Id: I8149f68437b4604fc79ac7f1e5a2811f9a706dfa

commit_message:
Huawei: Modify array LUNs naming rules

We use the first 8 chars in the uuid string and hash
value of uuid to name array LUNs, We can establish
the relationship between the volume uuid and the array
lun name.

There is no need to rename lun on array in unmanage and
unmanage_snapshot, So we remove the rename calls.

Change-Id: Id4cdfc3b73a4c97fa2c14aa2afb361e643ab6369
Closes-Bug: #1570205

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-05 15:26:46.000000000', 'files': ['templates/keystone_nginx.conf.j2'], 'message': 'Fix nginx SCRIPT_NAME uwsgi_param

The SCRIPT_NAME uwsgi_param is passed to the client resulting in errors
such as:

UnknownConnectionError: Unexpected exception for
http://10.1.1.101:5000keystone-wsgi-public/v3/auth/tokens:
Failed to parse: 10.1.1.101:5000keystone-wsgi-public

We should default this to a blank string to ensure this works
appropriately.

Change-Id: I3da36f8e2281eefdbad903d438ffd93ddd2f5071
'}]
commit_message:
Fix nginx SCRIPT_NAME uwsgi_param

The SCRIPT_NAME uwsgi_param is passed to the client resulting in errors
such as:

UnknownConnectionError: Unexpected exception for
http://10.1.1.101:5000keystone-wsgi-public/v3/auth/tokens:
Failed to parse: 10.1.1.101:5000keystone-wsgi-public

We should default this to a blank string to ensure this works
appropriately.

Change-Id: I3da36f8e2281eefdbad903d438ffd93ddd2f5071

commit_message:
L2 Agent Extensions handle unimplemented methods

If an L2 agent extension does not implement the handle_port or delete_port
methods, we should check for that using hasattr() beforehand rather than
catching any AttributeErrors.  This is based on a conversation related to
identical code in the L3 agent extensions:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/339246/15/neutron/agent/l3/l3_agent_extensions_manager.py@44

Change-Id: Ic0c5133a9f49c39f1f446328beb3e0ca7eb85095

commit_message:
Do not send shared param when not allowed.

When a user changes the name of a network,
neutron returns a 403 error.
Even if the user only changes the name and doesn't
change the shared state, Horizon send
the shared data to neutron and neutron returns
 403 when the user doesn't have admin rights

Change-Id: I52726b7215acb877f38069c95d190eb36399954f
Closes-Bug: #1609467
(cherry picked from commit 28c443f4e320c4c35b650f0aedb1e6343c785be3)

commit_message:
Move Murano CFAPI configuration to separate config files

Since [1] CFAPI configuration is in separate config files:
as for main service configuration (murano-cfapi.conf) as for paste ini
configuration (murano-cfapi-paste.ini).

[1] https://blueprints.launchpad.net/murano/+spec/separate-service-broker-from-murano

Change-Id: I3e12452680e85c88adf45c68605d13d00932c020

commit_message:
keystone: configure credentials

Configure Keystone on the undercloud to generate credentials during
bootstrap.

This step is required with latest Keystone. Puppet will take care of
running keystone-manage credential_setup one time but won't do any
rotation or any export of the key yet.

Change-Id: I5439c634be8335884e395cde3f4d036524e10abb

commit_message:
Make magnum manage_template read config file and increase coverage

Currently magnum-manage-template command doesn't read config file
properly. This patch make manage-template script read config file
and display template list the right way.

Add new unit tests for cmd/template_manage.py.
Increase the coverage for cmd/template_manage.py from 0 to 100%.

subject: Revert "Revert "Pre-install pip/virtualenv packages""
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-07-14 03:56:51.000000000', 'files': ['elements/centos-minimal/environment.d/10-centos-distro-name.bash', 'elements/pip-and-virtualenv/install.d/pip-and-virtualenv-source-install/01-install-pip'], 'message': 'Revert "Revert "Pre-install pip/virtualenv packages""

This reverts commit a645fa4ffb3c819f38ce1c66e83eb409c587c55d.

It is really devstack causing problems here; it was removing the
python-virtualenv package & re-installing using pip (see depends-on).
This failed because the pip-install we did here removed the egg-file
that rpm expected to be there, so rpm bailed out on the removal.

But even if it worked, this just leads you back down the path of the
original problem; that the system packaged version can be re-installed
and overwrites the pip installed version.  Thus I still believe this
is the correct thing to do in the dib element.

Note it is not a common problem (devstack aside); most jobs don't
touch python-virtualenv & related packages (the one we did notice this
on was being brought over from travisci where it was required for some
reason).

Change-Id: I82acb865378a0fa5903a6267bfcee0e2962eced0
Depends-On: Ib0edf6c4ee8a510e9d671213de35d787f56acfed
'}]
commit_message:
Revert "Revert "Pre-install pip/virtualenv packages""

This reverts commit a645fa4ffb3c819f38ce1c66e83eb409c587c55d.

It is really devstack causing problems here; it was removing the
python-virtualenv package & re-installing using pip (see depends-on).
This failed because the pip-install we did here removed the egg-file
that rpm expected to be there, so rpm bailed out on the removal.

But even if it worked, this just leads you back down the path of the
original problem; that the system packaged version can be re-installed
and overwrites the pip installed version.  Thus I still believe this
is the correct thing to do in the dib element.

Note it is not a common problem (devstack aside); most jobs don't
touch python-virtualenv & related packages (the one we did notice this
on was being brought over from travisci where it was required for some
reason).

Change-Id: I82acb865378a0fa5903a6267bfcee0e2962eced0
Depends-On: Ib0edf6c4ee8a510e9d671213de35d787f56acfed

commit_message:
Remove the PVID Looper

With the ability to pass the VLAN over to nova, via the mechanism driver
and vif binding details, we no longer need the PVID Updater.

Previously the function would wait for nova to provision a VIF on VLAN
1.  Then the sea networking agent would detect this new port, update the
SEA to support the VLAN (if needed) and then update the VLAN on the VIF.

Now that we can pass the VLAN to Nova at the VIF create time, that last
step is not needed.

Change-Id: Ifc5bfe8b5e118f02faf0556cc3e67d11a66e2b25

subject: Change NeutronWorkers default to result in previous behavior
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-09-01 19:37:49.000000000', 'files': ['puppet/services/neutron-api.yaml'], 'message': 'Change NeutronWorkers default to result in previous behavior

Neutron's behavior changed in Newton with respect to the default value
of 0 for NeutronWorkers. Instead of effectively treating it as
"processorcount", it now assumes we mean what we say and doesn't spawn
any workers, resulting in only a single process for handling API
requests. This change alters the default value to regain the previous
behavior.

This change also extends the worker count to the RPC worker setting -
which was possibly an oversight in previous releases. The default
behavior will have no result for most systems.

Closes-Bug: 1619383

Change-Id: Id6e3ee544160372c806905e77348150a1a1eec1b
'}]
commit_message:
Change NeutronWorkers default to result in previous behavior

Neutron's behavior changed in Newton with respect to the default value
of 0 for NeutronWorkers. Instead of effectively treating it as
"processorcount", it now assumes we mean what we say and doesn't spawn
any workers, resulting in only a single process for handling API
requests. This change alters the default value to regain the previous
behavior.

This change also extends the worker count to the RPC worker setting -
which was possibly an oversight in previous releases. The default

commit_message:
Add 'library convergence' to Requirements mission

The current Requirements team mission is failing to mention an
important aspect of the team job, which is to try to get the
dependencies to converge toward the best-maintained library where
there are multiple variants used to get the same functionality.

Change-Id: I987bb346c666e41825dccc9b17eed42920d59361

commit_message:
Move pip_lock_to_internal_repo to group_vars

The pip_lock_to_internal_repo variable is repeated in most playbooks,
move it to all's group vars instead.

The repo_all group and lxc_hosts play are exceptions, overriding it to
False.

commit_message:
Resolve tasks by node tags

A 'tags' attribute has been added to each role in 'roles_metadata'.
Initially all non-controller roles will only have a tag of their own
role name. This will allow existing tasks which do not have tags
associated with them to work correctly. In the abscence of tags a
task's roles will be used to determine which nodes it will run on.

Implements: blueprint role-decomposition

Change-Id: I79d7ecced68e8a4cb5cafe6b4815d62ae0fe5f03

commit_message:
Add delete method for gnocchi to delete batch of resources

Add a method post_delete in gnocchi/rest/__init__.py to
accept an resource id list that contains ids to be deleted.
Add method delete_resources in gnocchi/indexer/sqlalchemy.py
to delete related data in db.
The HTTP request looks like:

    DELETE /v1/resource/<resource_type>
    Content-Type: application/json

        {"ids" [xx_id,xx_id...]}.

An corresponding gnocchi client CLI needs to be added later.

Change-Id: I6c2fbc7066dd45c974f2746ee1e555cd962cbb56
Partial-Bug: #1585262

subject: dvr_snat: properly track SNAT traffic
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-06 19:09:41.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/agent/l3/dvr_snat_ns.py'], 'message': 'dvr_snat: properly track SNAT traffic

When running DVR, it's possible for traffic to get confused and sent
through SNAT thanks to the way conntrack tracks "new" connections.  This
patch sets "nf_connctrack_tcp_loose" inside the SNAT namespace to more
intelligently handle SNAT traffic (and ignore what should be FIP
traffic).

Change-Id: If962e74313cd81ac00604dfc66727e553efe272f
'}]
commit_message:
dvr_snat: properly track SNAT traffic

When running DVR, it's possible for traffic to get confused and sent
through SNAT thanks to the way conntrack tracks "new" connections.  This
patch sets "nf_connctrack_tcp_loose" inside the SNAT namespace to more
intelligently handle SNAT traffic (and ignore what should be FIP
traffic).

Change-Id: If962e74313cd81ac00604dfc66727e553efe272f

commit_message:
Add Multi Region Swift gate scenario

* Fix networking so that we can extend it for MR swift gate.
* Add a vars file for region A and region B.
* Add host_vars and inventory files for region A and region B
* Split out the function-test to allow all scenarios to use the same
test.yml file.
* Use -e @vars-file.yml format in tox.ini since we can't include vars
files based on a variable.
* Remove any references to include_vars: test-vars.yml as a result of
moving to use -e @vars-file.yml
* Add static routes into host_vars for swift-proxy and swift-storage
hosts so that they can route to the other region.
* Make addresses in test-vars more generic based on inventory.

Change-Id: I52b4068acbc80dcb7710d388ccbed2edcb8bfd61

commit_message:
Add constraint to prohibit balance-tcp from BondInterfaceOvsOptions

This patch adds an allowed_pattern contraint that uses a negative
lookahead assertion to only allow options strings that do not contain
the 'balance-tcp' option.

commit_message:
Add rexray volume driver to Swarm

* Volumes are created using the bay's trusstee user
  scoped by the bay's trustID.
* In volume-service.sh it is checked if rexray exists
  in the image, so if you have built an image with
  rexray it will configure and start rexray service.

This change replaces:
Ie5e78e6b9d06fd2c92915b8635b8062c008e9696

Change-Id: I11043d5edcf73a87220c86320f9938b9347c118f
Partially-Implements: blueprint magnum-integrate-with-cinder

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary open call and related vars in unit tests

Since the methods touching exisiting file is mocked, we don't have to
open the file. (if it is needed, we should close at first anyway)

And cleanup unecessary vars/imports that is used for making the file
path.

This patch is a followup on:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/350471/

Change-Id: I8fbc0b5b9a01782b6da5a7dd674f52d4b566ca5c

commit_message:
Allow configuration of rabbitmq plugins

The rabbitmq_plugins variable was mentioned as a loop item but was not
actually being used within the task to enable the management plugin.

It can now be overridden to enable or disable any RabbitMQ plugins.

Change-Id: I35f82427be464c811ee098ef676825aaa1e05d8d
Related-Bug: 1617431

commit_message:
Proposal on supporting multiple Nova flavor

Currently Magnum can be used to provision a container cluster with one
Nova flavor for slave nodes and one flavor for master nodes. There are
some requirements that user want to provision a container cluster using
different Nova flavors for minion nodes.

commit_message:
Enable to update master_count propertys of bay

master_count property of bay is not defined in the bay_update_allowed_properties
which is used at the time of validating bay properties in validate_bay_properties.
master_count parameter was added in the allowed set of property.

Change-Id: Id8557b4139df96c0c867e6f6e09bc6ae39b6fbd9
Closes-bug: #1580491

commit_message:
Better namespace the list of TripleO actions

The action list is quite small, but growing rapidly and already
getting confusing. In the Python package we have more detailed
namespaces to group the actions - we should use the same to group
them for users too.

This adds the new entry points, but leaves the existing names
in place. These can be removed once the CLI and GUI have
transitioned over.

Change-Id: I247747c7d641a70f320faf109c15745d00d62ff3

commit_message:
Restore swift storage directory permissions after upgrade

Any update or reinstall glance-common package triggers
its postinst action with following command:
chown glance:glance -R /var/lib/glance/ /etc/glance/
We use /var/lib/glance/node by default as swift storage
folder http://goo.gl/97VJG2, and reinstallation of
glance-common breaks swift user access to it, so swift
services stop working. So, we need to fix /var/lib/glance/node
folder permissions right after upgrade command.
Also, the case of adding new controller node for already
updated cluster is covered.
This workaround is applied on when swift is enabled.

Closes-bug: #1618553
Related-bug: #1619282

Change-Id: Iea6ce51d6ed9fe42bba1b26b58ba43268a7f880c

commit_message:
Change the way Murano dashboard collects static with UCA packages

Horizon UCA packages collects static during installation
and doesn't recollect it if we use '--clear' option. It leads
to static absesnce. So we need to delete '--clear' option for
Murano dashboard collectstatic script when we use UCA packages

Change-Id: I9719208dff88ce4f3be1b038b8bb6a49a6ec387f
Related-Bug: #1603528
(cherry picked from commit 5e6d5d3233c27e7912182d8ff71ea19f2ba5939e)

commit_message:
Include both Trusty and Xenial gate-requirements-integration-dsvm

With the merge of Ia139c66e4e1daadae107b2fcdd0768d8d36bc984 we switched
to gating on ubuntu-xenial rather than ubuntu-trusty.  This uncovered a
small issue with the requirements gate and a larger issue for how we
correctly generate constraints during the transition from python3.4 to
python3.5.

This review adds back gate-requirements-integration-dsvm-ubuntu-trusty
so we can verify that we *can* correctly generate constraints for python
3.4 and python 3.5

Change-Id: I33e44578121c771e41d7068f9f020ecb87a9949f
Depends-On: I6acabf86933b7a7bce7baf44e6b512e7d0d2f6db
Related-Bug: 1620436

commit_message:
Fix module loading on centos hosts.

Introducing a new var: {{ openstask_host_module_file }} that contain
the path to the file containing module list.

Centos will use systemd-modules-load.service:
- http://www.unix.com/man-page/centos/8/systemd-modules-load.service/
- http://www.unix.com/man-page/centos/5/modules-load.d/

Change-Id: I9ce294045259752e48c47ed036a9550565f05bc5

commit_message:
Only admin can get actions with quotas

At present commands like 'cinder quota-defaults tenant_id'
(quota-show, quota-usage) display wrong info when tenant_id
is invalid. To check if the tenant-id/project-id is invalid
(or does not exist) the user should be admin. The test
test_quota_usage_after_volume_transfer invokes method get_defaults
in cinder/quota.py and if cls.alt_client is not admin he is not
authorized to perform the action to get project
(http://paste.openstack.org/show/558384/).

This patch is related to https://review.openstack.org/#/c/315673/

Change-Id: I2e6400330f5b1e2986cfb0ff86ea7c1c3ffa1e7b
Related-Bug: #1307487

commit_message:
Composable upgrades: cinder

Cinder-volume is kind of a special snowflake given that it can be
managed by pacemaker even in evolved HA arch (A/P on controllers) and
directly by systemd (e.g. on LVM block storage nodes), both in the same
deployment at the same time. So the cinder-volume role supports
upgrading such configurations.

Implements: blueprint overcloud-upgrades-per-service
Change-Id: I37a81c03131945824a9ef675dc3c80eff6033a87

commit_message:
Set max-servers value to 150 for internap-mtl01

First shalt thou create a change. Then shalt thou set the value to 150,
no more, no less. 150 shall be the number thou shalt set, and
the value of the config shall be 150. 151 shalt thou not set,
neither set thou 149, excepting that thou then proceed to 150.

Change-Id: Id2969000d18f600da15866a4f58834267323cfe2

commit_message:
Fix: Duplicated driver causes conductor to fail

This patch is fixing a problem which causes the conductor to get confused
and error out on startup in case there's a duplicated entry in the
enabled_drivers configuration option.

Closes-Bug: #1561564
Change-Id: Ib72bcde9b32d3c0b4b237068aa53146f58ea10a2

VMAX3 clone volume failure happens occasionally when
more than one thread is accessing the same storage
group at the same time. Extra locking has been put

Change-Id: Id6574d9e87a473ae5084ef39e341f4517758d66f
Closes-Bug: #1587654
'}]
commit_message:
VMAX Driver - VMAX3 clone volume failure

VMAX3 clone volume failure happens occasionally when
more than one thread is accessing the same storage
group at the same time. Extra locking has been put
around all config change operations involving storage
groups, to prevent this from happening.

Change-Id: Id6574d9e87a473ae5084ef39e341f4517758d66f
Closes-Bug: #1587654

commit_message:
Fix pep8 errors when running with python3

This patch is replacing raw_input() with six.moves.input() because
raw_input is not present in python3+.

Fixing this also makes "tox -epep8" happy when running with python3.

[{'number': 10, 'created': '2016-09-06 14:07:54.000000000', 'files': ['aodh/keystone_client.py'], 'message': "Restore trust workaround for legacy auth

Before mitaka, we were not supporting keystone v3 and we were
expecting to have the auth_url ending with /v2.0 to ensure
v2 keystone API. We were using a workaround to force v3 for trust
keystone client, and when we moved to keystoneauth1 we removed this workaround
but it's still needed.

This change restores it. It ensures the endpoint is a v3 endpoint when
the user enter a v2 endpoint and set domain to 'default' that was the
only that worked before, because we were not really support keystone v3.

This is not a backport because it fixes a bug in deprecated (and already removed from master) code.

Closes-bug: #1620499
Change-Id: Idf474348ab4d49073dc5561caf90e151c4138819
"}]
commit_message:
Restore trust workaround for legacy auth

Before mitaka, we were not supporting keystone v3 and we were
expecting to have the auth_url ending with /v2.0 to ensure
v2 keystone API. We were using a workaround to force v3 for trust
keystone client, and when we moved to keystoneauth1 we removed this workaround
but it's still needed.

This change restores it. It ensures the endpoint is a v3 endpoint when
the user enter a v2 endpoint and set domain to 'default' that was the
only that worked before, because we were not really support keystone v3.

This is not a backport because it fixes a bug in deprecated (and already removed from master) code.

Closes-bug: #1620499
Change-Id: Idf474348ab4d49073dc5561caf90e151c4138819

commit_message:
Release xstatic-angular-smart-table 1.4.13.2

As part of the improvements to the xstatic management and release
process, we have been using an xstatic-release[1] script to help with
creation and sanitisation of these packages. Unfortunately, an oversight
meant that the metadata of these packages was invalid, causing
downstream packagers to be unable to use them. This release updates the
metadata without changing the content of the package.

Relevant IRC log:
http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-release/%23openstack-release.2016-09-06.log.html#t2016-09-06T14:08:03

1. https://pypi.python.org/pypi/xstatic-release/1.2.1

Change-Id: I1433b5c984b0489351d04ac88e244f35ebb42c14

[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-09-02 15:22:59.000000000', 'files': ['manifests/profile/base/swift/ringbuilder.pp', 'lib/puppet/parser/functions/tripleo_swift_devices.rb'], 'message': 'Convert ringbuilder to build devices array

Currently we have some hard-coded mangling in t-h-t but we
instead need to build the array based on the nodes running swift
storage, combined with the SwiftRawDisks parameter.

This will enable running SwiftStorage on nodes other than Controller
and SwiftStorage roles, and is required for custom-roles due to
the hard-coded stuff in the role templates and overcloud.yaml

Change-Id: I11deed1df712ecccf85d36a75b3bd2e9d226af36
Partially-Implements: blueprint custom-roles
'}]
commit_message:
Convert ringbuilder to build devices array

Currently we have some hard-coded mangling in t-h-t but we
instead need to build the array based on the nodes running swift
storage, combined with the SwiftRawDisks parameter.

This will enable running SwiftStorage on nodes other than Controller
and SwiftStorage roles, and is required for custom-roles due to
the hard-coded stuff in the role templates and overcloud.yaml

Change-Id: I11deed1df712ecccf85d36a75b3bd2e9d226af36
Partially-Implements: blueprint custom-roles

commit_message:
Fixed assumed utility pip install for specific clients

This change implements a dynamic lookup and installation of python clients
within the utility container. The purpose of this change is to ensure that only
python clients known to the environment are installed within the utility
container.

Change-Id: I60e79f3017a5ad3eec6ffca36839acf50fbdf3ce
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Align the stars to promote Ci to latest Newton

1) Promote RDO to latest trunk
2) Configure puppet-keystone to manage credentials, as it's now required
   by keystone upstream.
3) Run Zaqar tests against API v2 (1.0 is deprecated and 1.1 will be
   deprecated soon).

Depends-On: I364f65c7009e400f2851e37999e1d8c0b6f5fd5a
Change-Id: I967038c872628a5a290e2890641c9c8dac45588d

Update ironic-multinode job timeout

configured on ironic-multitenancy job, since multinode job using the same
tests and configuration as ironic-multitenancy we using the same value.

commit_message:
Clean up FakeClient classes in volume fakes

Put FakeTransferClient and FakeServiceClient classes
into FakeVolumeClient class, I think we need not to
create FakeClient classes for every objects, we can use
only FakeVolumeClient for all volume objects. This can
reduce repetition, unified codes and make codes look
cleaner and easier.

Change-Id: I2729ef0e80166f4d49ccd9a48b653e2f215e3bfe

commit_message:
Update release configs with temporary file server IP

The ci.centos artifacts server was recently rate limited for
downloads, and this makes tripleo-quickstart pretty much unusable.

We have stood up a simple web server to host the files temporarily,
while we explore better options. This patch switches the default
image locations in the release configs to point to this new location.

Change-Id: I802b379b299c7e4232feed54273dc1919b968eae
